# polymarket.radar — env. EVERYTHING here is OPTIONAL.
# Out of the box (no .env at all) the dashboard reads Polymarket's public APIs
# directly and every board works. Copy to .env.local only if you need the extras
# below.

# --- Geo-restricted? Use your own reverse proxy ---
# Polymarket geo-blocks some regions. If you can't reach it directly, set this to
# your own transparent reverse proxy. It must forward:
#   /proxy/*    → https://clob.polymarket.com
#   /gamma/*    → https://gamma-api.polymarket.com
#   /data-api/* → https://data-api.polymarket.com
# Leave blank to hit the public APIs directly (the default).
POLYMARKET_PROXY_URL=
# Optional bearer token, only if your proxy requires one.
INFRA_API_TOKEN=

# --- Mother-cluster funding trace (Traders → "Mothers") ---
# This one feature traces wallet funding on Polygon via alchemy_getAssetTransfers,
# which public Polygon RPCs do NOT support — you need an Alchemy Polygon endpoint
# (free tier works). All OTHER boards work without it; if this is blank, the
# mother-cluster trace just shows "RPC not configured" and everything else runs.
POLYGON_RPC_URL=
